      "side": 1,
      "message": "So the reasoning behind the default UART was the following:\n- The UART address is taken from the device tree. It may change over time and FPGA build, so we don\u0027t want to hardcode this.\n- If we *crash* very early, or the DT is not available, than *any* attempt to print something is better than not even trying to print something. In the worst case the address is wrong, but we crashed already, so it doesn\u0027t really matter.\n\nSo normally the crash UART address is the same as the DT address, by design. There is only one UART that I know of, so we do not have an extra crash UART. It\u0027s just a fallback *guess* in case something goes wrong.",
